Table s 9 was prepared from the data in Appendix A.
It shows that the total number of workers who lived in each of these counties grew dramatically (i.e. between 21.7 percent and 44.1 percent) during the 1980s.
Table 9 also shows that the percentage of these workers who drove to work alone grew even more dramatically (i.e. between 24.1 percent and 59.9 percent) during the 1980s.
