Note that the number of residents in ` each county who chose to drive to work alone increased faster than the number of workers who lived in each county.
Orange County was the only one of the seven counties in which transit showed an increase in market share.
In 1980, 2.1 percent of Orange County residents commuted to work by public transit.
In 1990, 2.5 percent of these workers used transit.
However, the decline in the use of carpools and vanpools in Orange County offset the gains in transit ridership.
As a result, the' percentage of residents of Orange County who drove to work alone increased from 74.7 percent in 1980 to 76.7 percent in 1990.
The percentage of workers who shared rides to work declined in all seven counties.
